HEADWORD: Morphine
<hw>Mor"phine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From Morpheus: cf.
F. <ets>morphine</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A bitter white
crystalline alkaloid found in opium, possessing strong narcotic
properties, and much used as an anodyne; -- called also
<altname>morphia</altname>, and <altname>morphina</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

